[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has a rotten hand, and many players would just pass 1NT.

But WEST figures that having EAST play any 4-4 fit would be better than 1NT so 
he bids 2\C, Stayman. This is called "Garbage Stayman", and you can see why.

EAST bids 2\H and WEST passes. He would have passed 
either 2\S or 2\D also.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:AQ62.KJ8.A62.K87 T95.A732.J875.JT KJ73.Q95.KT4.Q93 84.T64.Q93.A6542"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "789a2466d448fac6eb4d036062dde95ea65fe9bd989b82ff03133f5fafda02bf"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{Just having a 4-card Major doesn't mean you must automatically use Stayman.

Here NORTH has a 4-card \S suit, but decides not to seek a 4-4 fit because his 
hand wouldn't have any ruffing values in a \S contract. He bids 3NT.

Notice that even though SOUTH also has four \Ss the 4-4 fit is not useful to them in 
a \S contract because neither hand can ruff any losers.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:KJ7.KJ54.KQ73.A5 53.T82.952.KJ972 QT864.Q73.A6.T84 A92.A96.JT84.Q63"]
